<participants>
{% for participant in participants %}
- {{ participant.full_name }}
{% endfor %}
</participants>

<raw_note>
{{ editor }}
</raw_note>

<transcript>
{{ words | timeline }}
</transcript>

{% if type == "TyprLocal" %}
Create a strategic summary that flows naturally and explains what happened in the meeting

Follow the format and guidelines from your system instructions.

IMPORTANT: Output only markdown. Do NOT include any XML tags like <raw_note>, <transcript>, or <participants> in your output.

Note: If raw_note contains relevant information, integrate it. Do not create sections for topics marked as "not mentioned".
{% elif type == "OpenAI" or type == "Groq" %}
Analyze this meeting transcript and create a strategic summary that flows naturally:

1. Group related discussions under meaningful business themes
2. For each theme, write bullets that naturally explain what happened and why it matters
3. Include the business context, decisions made, and what happens next
4. Write in conversational flow avoiding rigid labels
5. Use direct, action-oriented language, active voice
6. Make it feel like you're explaining to a colleague who missed the meeting
7. Keep the output proportional to complexity: short meetings should be brief; standard meetings usually need 3-6 sections; long or dense meetings may use up to 8 sections only when needed
8. Prefer fewer, denser bullets over many thin bullets, and omit low-signal discussion, repetition, greetings, and small talk

GOAL: Someone who didn't attend should understand the full picture and know exactly what they need to do.

IMPORTANT: Output only markdown. Do NOT include any XML tags like <raw_note>, <transcript>, or <participants> in your output.

Note: If raw_note says something was "not mentioned", do not create sections for those topics.
{% else %}
Create a concise but decision-complete summary combining the transcript and raw notes above. Follow your system instructions for format, proportional length, and style.

IMPORTANT: Output only markdown. Do NOT include any XML tags like <raw_note>, <transcript>, or <participants> in your output.

Note: If raw_note says something was "not mentioned", do not create sections for those topics.
{% endif %}
